		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Gatineau TOC june 4rth 2005<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=15343'>Simon "Whiplash" Ringuet</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=15343&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 9, 2005</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Pre-tournament : There was only one TOC that was close enough for me left and it was the one in Gatineau. 2 weeks from the even I hadn’t really any idea about what to play as since rotation hit with black rider release I played pretty much every week but I played so bad that I was about to forget the Gatineau TOC and settle for playing on day 1, but Kenneth won what seemed like a memorable online PSQ with a deck I was toying with since BR came out but I was playing with some really bad card choice and I wasn’t playing with enough pathfinding in my free peoples, so I decided to give a shot at this deck and I did fairly good before the tournament with it, playing pathfinders cause my well-travelled were in the mail from kwyjibo since I obviously decided to order them at the very last minute. I was pretty happy getting back from school Friday afternoon when I seen a padded envelope from Kwyjibo as those are really amazing. So I was all set except for my decklist whom I decided to, as usual, do at the last minute. I had to find a cool title for it but had no inspiration…I was getting really bad ideas when I seen that Reed was online on msn so I start chatting with him and he reminds me that he just recently turned 18 so half-joking, half-serious I tell him that I’ll have “Reed turned 18!” as my deck title, he finds it awesome and I have nothing better in mind so I keep that name. time to get to bed as I gotta wake early tomorrow for the ride.<br />
<br />
The Trip: It was the first time I was hitting the road for a LOTR tournament so it was obviously the first time I was going to that store in Gatineau. Patrick changed his mind at the last minute and chose to get there Friday night instead f Saturday morning to save him some road on Saturday morning so I’ll have to get there by my own, I get myself a map and there are 2 ways to get there either through Ottawa or staying in Quebec, according to my software it’ll take me around 2 and half hours to get there if I pass through Ottawa, I’d save about 15 minutes and 30 miles if I stay in Quebec on the old forest road, one good and one bad thing about my map, the good thing is that it looks pretty simple, the bad thing is that it looks WAY too simple so I’m pretty much sure to mis something on the way. So I leave home about 3 hours and 20 minutes early giving me a 50 minutes. So obviously I get out of the highway 50 a little too early so I have to pass through the city of Lachute, so while I was there I got to see something I never seen, that was a car with horns on the hood like in the old show Dallas! The “highway” that made me stay in Quebec was in fact a road that was at some place 30 mph and some other 55 mph, in one of the 55 mph zone there was a garage sale …like anyone would like to stop at that speed for a garage sale. Soon after I seen some weird sign of a farm that said :”Natural Beef”, so I passed as I wanted some nice synthetic  Beef. So after following a school bus on a while I get to the store exactly 50 minutes before the scheduled start after taking notes of those marvellous things to happen while I was driving, not that good of an idea after all.<br />
<br />
Tournament: So we are only 8 of the 24 expected by Eric cause lots of people have cancelled at the last minute for various good reasons and cause nobody got there from out of town except for me and Sullivan. Speaking of Sullivan he gets there at exacty 11:59:43 on my watch , that was a good thing he left Montreal Friday night heh, in fact the thing that screwed him was his passage in Ottawa, I’m kinda glad I stayed in Quebec heh. Since we are only 8 that’ll be 3 rounds so we take a lunch break before the tournament, we cross the street to McDonalds. Where Brian(I think it might as well been John) tripped over a kid and almost made him two dimensional.<br />
<br />
Game 1: Stephane Levesque Dwarves/Uruks<br />
I win the bid 1-0 and go first from trollshaw, I get Elendil narsil anduril derufin and faramirs toys thanks to trollshaw I double to 3 after playing another forest with anduril. He moves to 2 where I drop a couple of conditions, he tries to follow me into 3 so I drop the rest of the lost into the woods(so I have already 4 lost moving this way and hatred stired out!) and some random nazgul who get tharin lost into the woods but I forget to transfer to Durin, site 3 I play a well-travelled to get me another pair of forest and single easily into 4. He moves to 4 I play 2 Dark approach for Attea, Nelya and WK as well as grima who own both tharin and Durin so he has like 4 7 strength companions and I have 3 14+ strength  and grima so he pays a hone to make gimli survive against nelya but he gets a pair of nazguls on the fierce for the game)<br />
FW +3/3<br />
<br />
Now I’m getting pretty confident as I know that Pat has a bye already so I think I might need only one more win if I’m lucky on SOS <br />
<br />
Game 2: Michel Hevey (hobitses/Nazguls)<br />
The game details are getting pretty fuzzy from now on, and it’s not cause I waited like 5 days to write that TR I had no idea on what happened in the 2nd and 3rd games even after the tournament. I know that I tripled to 6 vs nothing with 8 fully healed companions. I have a total of 0 condition that survived through an entire shadow phase he had a lot of condition removal between minas morgul answers and buckland and he was destroying my site path pretty badly. I was doing nothing to his hobitses until site 5 where he dropped a bunch of them , I got a cople of kills there but nothing too interesting, same thing happened at 6 while I as at 8, I had the intention of dobling from 7 to 9 but get hit by a bunch of nazguls including a real huge black rider that overhelmed my Aragorn cause I didn’t see that +3 if 6 companions condition so I lose a couple of my nine guys there but not really the one I would plan on losing(Aragorn and garrison) when I have derufin and dervorin out so I’m down to 4 companions after site 8 and there are still 3 nazguls on the table so I let him move to 6. when I move to 9 I have 4 sapling and 4 comapnions so there is now way he will get me unless he gets like 6 nazguls out with like 14 pool he gets down 2 or 3.<br />
FW +3/3<br />
<br />
Game 3 Patrick Sullivan (Noble leaders/Forest Nazgulz)<br />
The lone thing I remember from this game is when we shared our deck titles, his was pretty awesome too(Ace of Bace)<br />
I pretty much know his deck although he made some last minute changes (including dropping the cards that he made me add(Grima)) we do not take that game too seriously (well our lunch games are generally less casual than that) I have no idea what happened this game but I got the full win and the bye to worlds!<br />
FW +3/3<br />
<br />
We get back home where I follow Pat until we get real near Montreal about 10 minutes after we split our ways alls me and tells me he’s stuck into traffic.<br />
<br />
Final standings :<br />
1 	 Ringuet, Simon 	 9 	 12	 7	 46 <br />
 2 	 Sullivan, Patrick 	 7 	 16	 9	 38 <br />
 3 	 Arseneault, Jean-Francois 	 7 	 12	 7	 46 <br />
 4 	 Cain, John 	 7 	 10	 5	 44 <br />
 5 	 hevey, michel 	 5 	 16	 9	 34 <br />
 6 	 Houle, Sébastien 	 5 	 14	 7	 40 <br />
 7 	 McDonald, brian 	 5 	 14	 7	 36 <br />
 8 	 Levesque, Stephane 	 3 	 14	 9	 40 <br />
<br />
Props:<br />
Patrick from coming down there too and for the grima splash<br />
Eric for running a real nice tournament<br />
All my opponents cause I had mad fun all day<br />
Every one that showed as this was a real nice even<br />
Kenneth for showing me the proper way to play the deck(I can’t believe I was playing that deck with little to no pathfinding)<br />
Reed cause he turned 18 and cause he got me a real nice deck title<br />
<br />
<br />
